This paper deals with the problem of online stochastic bin packing, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses Lagrangian relaxations and gradient descent, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization, making categories such as cs.LG, cs.IT, and cs.AI likely as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of heuristics and learning algorithms, which are also common in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
